meanings.definition: To rate higher than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: She was outrating her classmates in the spelling bee.
meanings.sent2: The new movie is outrating all the others at the box office.
meanings.sent3: The cat was outrating the dog in the race to the food bowl.
meanings.sent4: His dedication to practice was outrating his natural talent.
meanings.sent5: The sun outrating the moon in brightness.

meanings.sent3: The outrating of the team's performance was unexpected.
